      • predecessor

        public java.lang.String predecessor(java.lang.String key)
        Gets the largest key in the dictionary that is smaller than the input key. Returns null if the input key is not present or is the first entry.

        Requires two traversals through the list, one to locate the input key and second to locate its predecessor.

        TODO: Return predecessor even if input key is not present i.e. floor

      • successor

        public java.lang.String successor(java.lang.String key)
        Gets the smallest key in the dictionary that is greater than the input key. Returns null if the input key is not present or is the last entry.

        Requires two traversals through the list, one to locate the input key and second to locate its successor.
